article.headline: Liberty 79, High Point 66
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Larry Blair scored 23 points and Liberty used a 20-3 first-half run to take control Saturday night on its way to a 79-66 victory against High Point. The Flames (6-10, 3-1 Big South) used the big early run to take a 20-9 lead and built it to 41-24 by halftime. High Point (10-5, 3-1) got no closer than eight thereafter. Gabe Martin added 14 points and David Dees 12 for the Flames, who won their third straight. Liberty had seven 3-pointers -- four by Blair -- and the Panthers hit just one. Jerry Echenique led High Point with 16 points and Zione White had 13.
